target.message:
Quick fix for phasematrix buffered mode, forcing output to be on every experiment
Should be reverted once labscript implementation of StaticDigitalOutput for phasematrix is fixed (needs pseudoclock parent faked)

Move new_rep_name to runmanager, since the runmanager compilation queue
uses it too now.

Inform runmanager how many shots are remaining each iteration of the queue.
This is a bit of a hack presently, it happens in the queue's thread
and so blocks for up to 5 seconds if runmanager is not running.

It would be better done as an extension that the queue pipes events to.

Unconditionally convery h5_file paths to network agnostic when sending
to workers. Have a method in the worker convert them to local again
before calling the worker's transition_to_buffered().

Since shared_drive.path_to_local is idempotent, this is backward compatible
with devices that convert the path to local manually.
Working on adding base classes for the classes involved in making plugins.

Interpret loading from saved data of blank stylesheet as implying the
default should be used. However, append '\n' to an actual blank stylesheet,
so that upon saving and loading, it can be recognised as an intentionally blank
one. This is for backward compatibility with the fact that an empty string
used to be what was stored when no changes to the default stylesheet had
been made.
added a few more messages to the outbox
Remove bogus NEWS entries from labscript_utils

Fix crash upon clicking abort.
Remaining issue: abort doesn't actually abort until after the shot starts.
Need to make queue manager check abort status earlier.
